column4: hint
The location comes via location services. Accuracy is required to be within 30 meters, so make sure you are outside with a clear view of the sky.
This is a unique facility ID that links the inspection back to the SWMFAC table.
The six digit BMP number
Comma separated initials of each inspector with no spaces, e.g. ERP,BEW,EA
column6: Invalid entry for Inspector Initials. Check the format.
column8: At least one inspector initials is required

column4:
Not Rated (NR) means that the inspector could not access the feature to inspect. Not Rated is the default choice.

Not Scored (0) means that the inspection parameter is not part of the BMP design. Certain scores do not have a Not Part of BMP Design rating because they must be scored.
Scores the relative visibility of the facility from surrounding roadways, office complexes, shopping centers, residential areas, or other areas.
Scores the areas requiring routine mowing and slope considerations for allowing the mowing function to take place.
Scores the existence of a maintenance access road and, if it exists, how well is it designed to meet SHA criteria.
Describes issues relating to accessing a BMP site for field inspection or remedial actions.
Scores the overall condition of the BMP related to the physical presence of unwanted woody / leafy material, garbage accumulations, and sedimentation that possibly can block the outlet structure.
Scores the fencing condition by considering placement and structural condition when fencing exists to secure the BMP (other than right-of-way fencing).
Evaluates the evidence of trespassing, temporary habitation, or downstream occupancy.
Scores the <u>potential</u> for trespassing or temporary habitation based upon surrounding land uses.
column8: Potential for Public Hazard is a required selection.

column4: This parameter must be evaluated during the growing season from May 15 to October 30; otherwise the specific vegetation cannot be adequately assessed.

Should be scored during the growing season from the dates of May 15 to October 30. Site vegetation will always have a score of NR if inspection is being conducted between Oct 30th and May 15th unless conditions warrant a 3,4,5 rating of the parameter
Scores the overall condition of the BMP related to residue of contaminants from nearby activities or non-point source pollution within the watershed.
Scores the BMP feature(s) relating to pretreatment of stormwater prior to entering the treatment area.
Scores the condition of flows into a BMP such as areas of sheet flow, swales, and storm drains discharging into the BMP.
Scores the overall impact of the discharges into a BMP and their adverse effects that may impair the performance of the BMP.
Scores the overall downstream channel conditions beyond the SHA ROW.
Scores the stability of flow conveyance through the stormwater treatment area.

This parameter scores the overall vegetative condition of the upstream slope of the embankment, including within 15 feet of the embankment toe, related to type, size and percent coverage. Typically, this is scored during the growing season from May 15 to October 30.
Scores the condition of the upstream embankment stability related to erosion.
column8: Upstream Embankment Erosion is a required selection.

column4: Scores the condition of the upstream stability within 15 feet of the upstream toe of embankment.
column8: Upstream Embankment Toe is a required selection.

column4: This parameter scores the overall vegetative condition of the downstream slope of the embankment, including within 15 feet of the embankment toe, related to type, size and percent coverage. Typically, this is scored during the growing season from May 15 to October 30.
Scores the condition of the downstream embankment stability related to erosion.
column8: Downstream Embankment Erosion is a required selection.

column4: Scores the condition of the downstream stability within 15 feet of the downstream toe of embankment.
column8: Downstream Embankment Toe is a required selection.

column4: Scores the condition of downstream embankment related to water seeping out.
Scores the condition of the emergency spillway weir opening to function as designed when necessary.
column8: Emergency Spillway Opening is a required selection.

column4: Scores the stability of the emergency spillway relating to erosion of sides and bottom.
column8: Emergency Spillway Stability is a required selection.

column4: Scores the potential safety risk to the public due to deep water.
column8: Safe Water Depth is a required selection.

column4: Scores the accumulation of stormwater beyond 72 hours after a storm event resulting in loss of storage for water quality and / or detention.
Measurement of the depth of the excessive ponded water in the facility.
Scores the condition of BMPs with permanent standing water that is designed for water quality treatment.
Scores the opening of the low-flow orifice to allow for proper drainage of the BMP.
Scores the structural condition of the trash rack on the low-flow orifice.
column8: Orifice Trash Rack is a required selection.

column4: Scores the overall structural integrity of the riser weir or outlet structure.
Scores the openings of the riser structure, weir, or end-section (also headwall) to allow for proper flow through the spillway.
column8: Control Structure Opening is a required selection.

column4: Scores the amount of sediment accumulated inside the riser structure that could restrict the riser performance.
column8: Control Structure Sediment is a required selection.

column4: Scores the structural condition of the trash rack on the riser structure.
column8: Control Structure Trash Rack is a required selection.
Control Structure Trash Rack Photo required
Control Structure Trash Rack Subject required
Control Structure Trash Rack Comment required

column4: Scores the condition of the valves and associated appurtenances of the riser.
column8: Control Structure Valve is a required selection.

column4: Scores the condition of the outfall of the principle spillway and within 25 feet of the principal spillway structure.
Scores the overall condition of the principle spillway (pipe / barrel).
The following scores summarize some (but not all) of the ratings in the form above. This set is most useful in determining the overall rating.

BMP as observed in the field matches the set of plans being reviewed.
